At least four people were killed and dozens more are believed missing after a ferry capsized in the Shitalakkhya River in Narayanganj on the outskirts of the Bangladeshi capital Dhaka on Sunday afternoon, according to a local police official. Police inspector Aslam Mia said that the ferry was believed to be carrying more than 60 people, while 22 people had safely swum ashore after the accident. (With input from agencies)